        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Firefox Version 38'); ?>
        <p>Both <strong>Firefox 38</strong> and Firefox 38 ESR were released on 12 May 2015, with new tab based preferences, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Ruby', 'L'); ?> annotation support and availability of WebSockets in web workers, along with the implementation of the BroadcastChannel API and other features and security fixes.</p>
        <p>Firefox 38.0.1 and ESR 38.0.1 were released on 14 May 2015 for desktop, fixing a number of stability issues. Firefox 38.0.1 for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Android', 'OS'); ?> was released on 15 May 2015, fixing a number of stability issues.</p>
        <p>Firefox 38.0.5 was released on 2 June 2015 for desktop and Android, fixing bugs and security issues, and adding new functionality that included integration of Pocket and availability of Reader View mode. This was the first release offered to the Release channel users since 38.0.1.</p>
